## Overview

This project is a modern, serverless-ready blog application built with Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and a stylish frontend. It allows users to create, view, and delete blog posts with a responsive UI. The backend can be deployed locally or to cloud platforms like AWS.

---

## Prerequisites

Before setting up the project, ensure you have the following installed:

1. **Node.js** (v14 or higher)  
   - [Download Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)
2. **MongoDB** (Local or Atlas Cloud)  
   - [Download MongoDB Community Server](https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community)  
   - [Sign up for MongoDB Atlas](https://www.mongodb.com/atlas)
3. **AWS CLI** (for serverless deployment)  
   - [Install AWS CLI](https://aws.amazon.com/cli/)
4. **Git** (for version control)  
   - [Download Git](https://git-scm.com/)

